 *
 * native_sim has no DAC controller and no GD32 supervisor bridge.
 * The alp-dac0 alias resolves to a NULL spec, so alp_dac_open()
 * returns NULL with last_error = ALP_ERR_NOT_READY and the example
 * prints its diagnostic + "[dac] done" and exits.  This overlay
 * exists so the build resolves cleanly on native_sim/native/64 the
 * same way the sibling adc-voltmeter example does (the DAC is the
 * output half of the same <alp/adc.h> analog-converter surface).
 *
 * Auto-loaded by Zephyr when building for native_sim/native/64.
 */
